06/07/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Foreign Ministry State Secretary Hido Biscevic met on Monday (5 July) with Serbian Deputy Minister for Emigrants Aleksandar Cotric to discuss ethnic minority issues. 
While Cotric praised the treatment of ethnic Serbs in Croatia, Biscevic asked about the recent desecration of tombstones at a Croatian cemetery in Serbia. 
He requested that the Serbian government take steps to prevent further incidents.
Also Monday, Croatian Foreign Minister Miomir Zuzul and Justice Minister Vesna Skare-Ozbolt visited The Hague, meeting with chief UN war crimes prosecutor Carla del Ponte and UN tribunal President Theodor Meron. 
All parties agreed not to disclose the focus of their talks.
In other news, a court in Zagreb has ordered the state to pay 94,000 euros in damages to the family of an ethnic Serb who was killed during the war. 
Nikola Kostic was abducted from his home by military police in February 1992 and killed. 
Former President Franjo Tudjman granted amnesty to Kostic's murderer after only four months in jail. 
(Vjesnik, Dnevnik, Vecernji List - 06/07/04; HINA, HRT, AFP - 05/07/04)
